      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How does AssessIQ differ from Mercer Mettl for Indian IT companies?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "AssessIQ is designed specifically for structured, auditable B2B hiring decisions — with anchor-based rubrics, scoring bands, and full attempt logs that let teams defend every shortlist decision. Mercer Mettl offers a wider enterprise assessment library and a large-scale proctoring infrastructure. For Indian IT companies that need a focused coding-and-skills screening workflow with transparent scoring rationale, AssessIQ is the more direct fit. For enterprise exam programs, certification delivery, or very large question library breadth, Mercer Mettl is worth evaluating."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Does AssessIQ support AI-powered proctoring like Mercer Mettl?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "AssessIQ's proctoring layer includes browser tab-switch detection, full-screen enforcement, webcam monitoring with anomaly flagging, copy-paste restriction, and a timestamped event log per attempt. Mercer Mettl is known for AI-powered proctoring at very large scale, including their recognition in Gartner's proctoring category. The right choice depends on the scale of your exam program and what oversight the proctoring output needs to support."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is Mercer Mettl suitable for small and mid-size Indian companies?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Mercer Mettl serves a wide range of business sizes from startups to enterprises. Some user reviews note that pricing can be a consideration for smaller organizations. AssessIQ is designed with Indian team sizes and hiring workflows in mind, and offers a free starting point. Both platforms are worth evaluating based on your volume and feature requirements — check current pricing directly with each vendor."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Which platform has a larger question library — AssessIQ or Mercer Mettl?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Mercer Mettl publicly states a library of 100,000+ technical questions across many domains. AssessIQ's question packs are curated for Indian IT hiring role stacks — Python, Java, SQL, React, .NET, aptitude, and logical reasoning — with an emphasis on quality and calibration for Indian candidate pools rather than breadth alone. If raw library count is the primary criterion, Mercer Mettl has more volume. If calibration for Indian hiring contexts matters more, AssessIQ's curated approach is designed for that."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can I try AssessIQ before committing?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. AssessIQ has a free starting point — you can create an account and run assessments without a credit card. This makes it practical to evaluate the platform against your real hiring workflow before deciding."
      }
    }
  ]
};

